[decisions]
- Treat abuse.ch ingestion as operationally fixed for live data flow.
- Track the `fetched_count=0` queued-sync discrepancy as a separate follow-up instead of blocking the compose/env fix on it.

[mistakes and lessons]
- For composite feeds, checking only the parent feed state is insufficient; the subcomponent flags and container env propagation must be verified explicitly.
- When a queued job claims zero fetched items, validate the connector directly before assuming the upstream provider is empty or failing.

